e developing world faces a growing disconnect between the value of its resources and the availability of finance. What are the remedies for eliminating this disparity? Root shows us how to close the growing wealth gap among nations by building institutions that convert uncertainty into risk. Comparing China to India, Latin America to East Asia, and contemporary to historical cases, he offers lessons that can help the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund to tackle the political incentives that are the source of poor governance in developing nations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aEconomic developmentxPolitical aspects. 0aEconomic policy. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Economic Development.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/978140088019540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400880195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400880195.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles